    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-28T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1663.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-28T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1915—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Answering your January 27. You are instructed to support the President in
                    enforcing his orders for removal of governor of Puerto Plata and for resistance
                    to Vidal’s activities. Navy Department has been asked to send ship <hi
                        rend="italic">Castine</hi> to Puerto Plata.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
